data.description: Perched atop a hill on a secluded, oversized half-acre lot a short walk to Hideaway’s Middle Lake Marina, this recently renovated three bedroom, two bath, 2705 sq ft home boasts new floors, windows, interior and exterior paint, siding, and roof. Two large living areas and an open dining area compliment a spacious kitchen with beautiful granite countertops, under mount lighting, and eating area. An instant hot water heater services the filtered kitchen faucet and dishwasher. A bar and butler’s pantry and built-in secretary with shelves provides an elegant detail to the kitchen area. Off the kitchen is a large walk-in pantry with built-in cabinets and countertop and space for an additional fridge or freezer. The hall bathroom features a floating countertop of black granite and dimmable under-counter lighting. The laundry room is conveniently located off the hall with dual access to the primary bedroom suite. The primary bedroom features its own HVAC unit, a remote-controlled fireplace, custom mantle complete with dimmable outlets, and a one-of-a-kind peacock stained-glass window. The primary bath has a walk-in shower, free standing soaking tub, leathered granite, double vanities, and walk-in closet with plenty of cabinets and drawers equipped with electrical plugs hidden from view. As part of the recent remodel, a detached 811 sq ft three-bay carport with an art studio/office/playroom upstairs has a split A/C, vinyl plank flooring, storage, and space to add an additional bathroom. The carport is fully equipped to house all of your tools and outdoor accessories. A 569 sq ft workshop, greenhouse, and top-of-the-line three-person American Spa with Bluetooth rounds out the tasteful and expedient backyard area. Sprinkler system covers the front & back yards. Hideaway offers resort-style living with 24/7 security, three lakes, 27-hole golf course, a community Olympic-sized pool and multiple parks. Hideaway is in Lindale ISD, rated one of the top school districts in TX.
